text:
5G tested in Ukraine in six cities

07 Nov 2019, 09:45

Fifth generation (5G) communications technology is being tested in six cities of Ukraine. The National Commission for State Regulation in the Field of Communications and Informatization (NKRSI) allowed conducting such tests, as reported by the Babel, citing the press service of the department.
Tests will be held at the following addresses:

Kiev, Bessarabskaya square, 2;
Kiev, st. Antonovich, 175 (TC "Ocean Plaza");
Dnipro, European Boulevard, 2;
Kharkiv, st. Yaroslav the Wise, 33a;
Lviv, Liberty Avenue, 6/8;
Odessa, st. Deribassovskaya, 19;
Cherkasy, st. Smelyanskaya, 36.

5G will be tested by Ericsson Ukraine and lifecell mobile operator. Tests will be held from December 1, 2019 to May 31, 2020.
Communication will be tested at the base stations of the Radio DOT System, but their functions will be limited: only the Internet will be available, without voice communication.
